



What is the best way in C to convert a number to a string?

Solution: Use sprintf() function.


#include<stdio.h> 
int main() 
{ 
    char result[50]; 
    float num = 23.34; 
    sprintf(result, "%f", num); 
    printf("\n The string for the num is %s", result); 
    getchar(); 
} 




































































